.TH SIMPLE_SHELL "1" "28 Noviembre 19" "Simple Shell Manual Page"

.SH NAME
.B lsh 
-a simple holberton shell project
.PP

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./lsh
.PP

.SH Description
This is a simple command language interpreter capable of executing commands read
from standard input. This shell is also capable of having commands piped in from
the background.

.SH Overview
The shell is a program that reads lines from either a file or the terminal,
interprets them, and  executes other commands. Commands can be typed
directly to the running shell or can be piped in.

.SH Invocation
Shell could be run in interactive mode where input is accepted from
the keyboard. It also works in a non-interactive mode, the shell is run from a script or
standard input from a echo standard output.

.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
.RS information on built-in commands
.B  exit
- Shell process is terminated, and exit from it.
.PP
.B  env
- Print all the environmental variables of this shell.

.SH Command Exit Status
A command exits with zero for success, any other value indicates failure
or error.

.SH Pipelines
This shell does not handle with pipelines |.

.SH Special Parameters
.IP None
This shell does not handle with special characters.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.IP HOME
Automatically set from the user's login direcotyr. Default argument for the
cd builtin.
.IP PATH
Default search for executables.

.SH SEE ALSO
sh(1)

.SH BUGS
No known bugs.

